2. (30 points) Two of the languages below are context free. One is not. Prove one of the languages IS context free by drawing the state machine for a PDA corresponding to it. Prove one of the languages IS context free by giving a CFG for it. For the language that is NOT context free, show the first three steps of the pumping lemma proof (1. Assume CF, 2. Let p be the pumping length, 3. Choose a string …), list all cases for the decompositions, and work out two overlapping-character subcases (‘v in a’s, x in a’s & b’s,’ etc.).

a. L2a = {a^r b^s c^t | r > s, s > t, t > 0, r < 4}

b. L2b = {a^r b^s c^t d^q | r = t; s < 2q; q,r,s,t > 0}

c. L2c = {a^r b^s c^t d^q | r = q, s < t; r,q,s,t > 0}
